channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Woman arrested in alleged scheme to defraud Presley family through Graceland sale
item.description: A woman was arrested Friday morning in connection with an alleged scheme to defraud Elvis Presley's family out of millions of dollars and the ownership of Graceland.

item.title: Metro Atlanta police were looking for stolen cars, but they also found massive amount of drugs, guns
Secret Service approves bulletproof glass for Trump's outdoor rallies
item.description: In the wake of last month's assassination attempt, the Secret Service has approved a new plan to allow bulletproof glass to shield former President Donald Trump during his outdoor rallies. The shields are already used for sitting and vice presidents, but until now hadn't been deployed for candidates. CBS News congressional correspondent Scott MacFarlane has more.

item.title: Harris to back grocery price-gouging ban. Here's how it would work
item.description: Economists who spoke to ABC News disagreed sharply over the measure.

item.title: Ford recalling about 85,000 Explorer police vehicles because of potential for an engine fire
8/16: CBS News 24/7 Episode 1
item.description: Ernesto targets Bermuda as Category 2 hurricane; Thousands pack London's Wembley Stadium for Taylor Swift's "Eras Tour" amid tightened security.

item.title: North Korea to partially reopen doors to tourism for 1st time since COVID-19 pandemic
item.description: North Korea is set to partially reopen its doors to tourism later this year after being closed off since January 2020, according to a Chinese-based tourist operator.

item.title: Stow police offer new details on suspected murder-suicide at Taco Bell
Why you should put $10,000 into a long-term CD before September
item.description: If you're going to deposit $10,000 in a long-term CD account, you may want to do it before next month. Here's why.

item.title: Settler rampage in West Bank sparks rare condemnation from Israeli leaders
item.description: Israeli leaders have roundly condemned a settler attack that killed one Palestinian and torched homes and cars in the occupied West Bank

item.title: Belarus says there is a high chance of armed provocation from Ukraine
Gaza cease-fire negotiations resume, Israeli settlers attack village in West Bank
item.description: Negotiations for a cease-fire in Gaza resumed Friday in Qatar as the war between Israel and Hamas continues. Israeli forces have ordered new evacuations in parts of the enclave that had previously been designated civilian safe zones. BBC News correspondent Jenny Hill has more on the cease-fire talks and an attack in the West Bank.

item.title: Texas couple charged with failing to seek medical care for injured 12-year-old who later died
item.description: A Texas couple has been charged following the death of a 12-year-old girl who authorities say lay unconscious for four days before medical treatment was sought
